data.title: Night Four Concert — Bitter Jester Foundation for the Arts, NFP
data.meta_description: Information about the performers and judges appearing at the Night Four Concert of the Bitter Jester Music Festival’s seventeenth season, 2023. Judy’s Pizza and Ravinia Brewing Co. will be on-hand all night long serving food, beer, and wine! Val’s halla Records will be selling turntables and vinyl,
data.meta_site_name: Bitter Jester Foundation for the Arts, NFP
data.text:
Big Dune Avenue is a rock band based in Valparaiso. Formed in 2019, the band has performed at local music festivals and numerous basements around Northwest Indiana. Coming from different musical backgrounds, their sound is a unique mix of Sonic Youth and the Rolling Stones. Their dynamic sound and unique chemistry captivates audiences, leaving them wanting more.

Christine Compall's singing career began in Childrens Theatre. After her father gave her a guitar for her 10th birthday she became enthralled with singing and playing the instrument. Her musical style is primarily Pop and Country influenced. Christine used the downtime during Covid to write her own originals and, once restrictions were lifted, she began singing them at local restaurants on the Chicago's North Shore.

Formed by four high school friends, Exit 122 is a Pop Punk band characterized by their fun and energetic sound, featuring driving rhythms, melodic lead guitar, and catchy choruses. The band combines elements of Easycore, Grunge, and Emo with Pop Punk to create a unique sound that has echoes of Blink 182, New Found Glory, and My Chemical Romance.

Flannel Folk is a contemporary a cappella group based in Cedarburg. Since 2018, the ensemble has been wowing fans in Southeast Wisconsin and Northern Illinois with their original unique arrangements of fun and energetic music of numerous genres, including Doo-wop, 80's Rock, modern hits, and originals.

Free Joel is a Rock n’ Roll band representing Valparaiso, Muncie, and New Palestine. Their songs are defined by Blues, Funk, and Classic Rock roots; a combination of nostalgic dance tunes that will get you moving. As young adults, Free Joel leaves a lasting impression on audiences by interacting with the crowd and bringing a high energy to all their shows.

Jackson Wagner is a progressive Metal guitarist and producer from Sioux City. Known for his crushing, melodic, and technical riffage, Wagner picked up a guitar at the age of 15. Now an 18-year-old, he has publicly released two tracks, "Wishful Thinking" and "Electric Shores," to major streaming platforms, with many more on the way.

Lake Drive is a New Age Hair Band from Milwaukee. They continune to reach a growing fanbase with their compelling catalog of music mixed with their vibrant stage presence. Lake Drive's reminds crowds of their favorite artists, creating an incredibly diverse, yet pinpointed sound that has been described as "Pop Rock, Alternative Emo, and Indie Rock.

Lo-Fi Killers is a Hard Rock duo from the Madison area. With Caleb's octave fuzz guitars and Jack's hard-hitting drums, the two-man band creates a unique take on the Rock genre. Borrowing from artists such as Soundgarden, Black Sabbath, and Royal Blood, the band showcases an ability to be both heavy and catchy.

Caleb Broadhurst began writing songs at the age of 12. A self-taught guitarist and producer, he has been playing around the Chicago area (where he currently resides) and throughout the Midwest for years. His debut EP, which he wrote and produced for the project "Pumpkin Milk" was released in July of 2022 and includes six self-produced tracks. His influences include Elliot Smith and The Slaps, to name just two.

Sorry Machine is an artsy Punk quartet from Madison. Formerly known as "You Got the Message," Sorry Machine's sound has changed drastically and has been refined over the past year. The band always looks for ways to diversify its sound and they are very excited to showcase these changes at Bitter Jester. 2023!
